Topic: A named stream of messages in Kafka.

Producer Group: A set of producers that work together to send messages to a topic.

Topic Partitioning: Dividing a topic into multiple partitions for scalability and parallel processing.

Offset: A unique identifier for a message in a partition.

Consumer Group: A set of consumers that work together to consume messages from a topic.

Consumer Instances: Individual consumer processes that belong to a consumer group.

Consumer Rebalancing: Reassigning partitions to consumer instances when a consumer joins or leaves the group.

ZooKeeper: A distributed configuration and coordination system used by Kafka to manage the cluster.
